# 📘 Day 9 – File Integrity Monitoring (FIM) with Wazuh

## 🧭 Objective
The objective of this lab was to configure and analyze File Integrity Monitoring (FIM) using Wazuh. The goal was to detect file changes in real time, investigate generated alerts, and perform SOC-style analysis including risk assessment and MITRE ATT&CK mapping.

---

## 🖥️ Lab Environment
- OS: Kali Linux  
- SIEM: Wazuh Agent v4.7.3  
- Monitoring Tool: Wazuh Syscheck (FIM)  
- Monitoring Scope: `/home/sheik/fim-lab`, `/etc/passwd` (simulated incident)  
- User: root / sheik  

---

## 📌 FIM Overview

File Integrity Monitoring (FIM) is a security capability that tracks changes to files and directories in real time or at scheduled intervals.

Wazuh FIM detects:
- File creation
- File modification
- File deletion
- Permission changes
- Ownership changes

It is commonly used to detect:
- Unauthorized system changes
- Malware persistence
- Privilege escalation attempts
- Configuration tampering

